room_title: Escape room "Ancient Egypt" by FLEE in Seattle
room_description:
You were super excited about an invitation from your archaeology professor, Dr. Stanley, to join his Egyptian expedition. However, upon arrival after a very exhausting trip, you are informed that Professor Stanley has been missing for days. His last known trip was to King Tut's tomb. You noticed that the stamped date on the invitation was the same day he has gone missing. Could this be more than a coincidence?
You and other crew members decided to search for Professor Stanley. Upon entry of King Tut's tomb, the stone door suddenly collapsed behind you. You've been wandering and exploring with your team but mysterious forces have led you astray from your destination. Will you be able to find the hidden path and lead your team out? Or will you meet your demise wandering until death within the chambers?
